# UX #2: an UNKNOWN rc from the download must never claim "check Wi-Fi" — honest unknown-cause
# copy pointing at the log; stub intact; launch proceeds (#3 expectation line, minus the
# fix-the-connection coda no unknown cause can promise).
desc fetch hook: unknown rc -> unknown-cause copy (never "check Wi-Fi"), stub intact
invoke prehook
config paired
romarg Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba
sdfile Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba
engine 9|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace SHOW2 simple text='Couldn't download Zelda — unknown cause, try again (details in last-sync.log). The game screen that follows will fail to open — that's expected.'
expect_trace_absent check Wi-Fi
expect_file_empty Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba
